The nodes_tbl contains 1,159 rows and 31 columns, including attributes like type, label, sub_type, and content. Meanwhile, the edges_tbl captures 3,226 connections among these nodes, indicating the flow of communication or relationships via source, target, and type.
To understand the distribution of node types, we generate a quick summary:

table(nodes_tbl$type)


      Entity        Event Relationship 
          72          802          285 


Most nodes represent Events, which includes communication, assessments, and movements. These are the core of the graph‚Äôs activity and will be our main focus moving forward. The remaining nodes represent Relationships (such as colleagues) and Entities (such as people and vessels).
This breakdown helps guide our filtering in the next steps‚Äîparticularly in isolating Communication Events and linking them to relevant people, vessels, and aliases for Questions 2 and 3.
